model.hed: From Cool Denim Jackets to Cozy Fall Coats, These Are The Best Street Style Looks at London Fashion Week
model.dek: The temperatures may be cooling down, but the fashion is heating up.

items.caption: Season after season, London Fashion Week continually brings the heat when it comes to fierce street style looks. There just seems to be some sort of creative energy at work that encourages people to really *do them* when it comes to getting dressed in the morning. From models off duty to editors and the ever-present fashion students, see what the best dressed Londoners are wearing this fashion week.
Layered knits are sure to keep you warm this fall.
We are feeling this fringe for fall.
We've been seeing the [bomber jacket](http://www.teenvogue.com/gallery/nathalie-emmanuel-teen-vogue-october-2015) everywhere lately, and we're loving it.
This bag is stoping traffic — literally.
Proof that you can never have to many prints among friends.
This pale blue fleece looks *so* cozy, we need one ASAP.
Keeping it neutral.
Our eye doesn't know where to look first, and it's not a bad thing.
A perfect example of the versatility of a classic denim jacket.
A huge smile is always the best accessory.
The Man Repeller's Leandra Medine adds a cozy fall sweater to her feminine skirt.
Looking pretty in pink.
Rocking a cool blue color palette from head to toe.
Any ensemble that incorporates a cool graphic tee is a winner in our book.
Comfy knit pants are all we want to wear this season.
So many rad layers in this look.
Pairing denim in different washes instantly adds interest to any look.
Everyone should invest in a great statement coat for the season.
A feminine tie-neck blouse perfectly balances out a pair of boyfriend jeans.
Model Langley Fox transitions her silky summer pants thanks to a coordinating turtleneck.
Going bold in head-to-toe prints.
Dree Hemingway proves silk track pants can look ultra luxe.
Bringing back the '90s in grunge inspired looks.
Stripes on stripes on stripes.
A classic tartan scarf will always be a fall staple.
That shearling sure looks cozy.
Floaty dresses in longer lengths are perfect for fall.
When your favorite stuffed animal doubles as a purse.
Making the case for co-ords this fall.
Loving model Binx Walton's sporty style in the London streets.
Showing some old school Tommy Hilfiger style — logo-mania is back and better than ever.
A peek-a-boo back slit instantly grabs your attention.
She's part of the [Marques'Almeida crew](http://www.teenvogue.com/gallery/teen-vogue-editors-wear-new-york-fashion-week/8).
Because a red, white, and blue moment isn't just for the Fourth of July.
A bright bag instantly elevates this ensemble.
Extra long sleeves add a sense of humor to this stylish look.
We always love a good distressed denim moment.
From their bright locks to their on-point accessories, we love everything about these fashionable friends.
The perfect transitional look: pair your sheer summer dress with a cozy knit.
Nothing completes an outfit like bright and bold sneakers.
Adding a printed coat to the top of our fall wishlist.
Kate Foley's dark fall florals are a fresh take on the feminine print.
A classic white button-up and leather skirt is a perfect pairing.
This awesome look proves the athleisure trend is still going strong.
*Teen Vogue's* Jessica Minkoff knows all about pattern play.

fields.name: Alexandra Thurmond
fields.bio:
__What sort of advice would you give your 18-year-old self?__  
I would tell myself to try as many different things as possible! College is an amazing time to experiment, indulge your interests, and find out what you’re truly passionate about.

__What fashion item seems to always be on your shopping list?__  
I’ve never met an awesome pair of wide leg (preferably printed) pants that I didn’t love—they’ve become my signature. Bring on the palazzos!
 
__What’s your go-to karaoke song?__  
No Doubt “Just a Girl” - Tragic Kingdom was the first CD I ever owned. I’ve always wanted to be Gwen Stefani, she is such a strong female figure and all around badass.

__What’s your favorite movie quote?__  
"It’s all happening.” From band-aid Penny Lane in Almost Famous (my all-time favorite movie!). She was all about living in the moment and never taking experiences for granted.
fields.title: Digital Fashion Editor
